issue.title: addressing #802
issue.body:
Fixes #802 

* [ ] Does this PR change the input/output behaviour of a cryptographic algorithm (i.e., does it change known answer test values)?  (If so, a version bump will be required from *x.y.z* to *x.(y+1).0*.)
* [ ] Does this PR change the the list of algorithms available -- either adding or removing?  (If so, PRs in OQS-OpenSSL, OQS-BoringSSL, and OQS-OpenSSH will also be required by the time this is merged.)

In case it matters - here's the build script I use, to simplify my life ;)
```bash
#!/usr/bin/env bash

DATE_START="`date`"

KEY_FILE="./CMakeLists.txt"
if ! grep -q liboqs "$KEY_FILE" ; then
   echo "We appear to be in the wrong directory (${PWD}) - exiting..."
   exit -1
fi

rm -rf build
mkdir -p build
cd build

env RUN_TESTS_PARALLEL=FALSE cmake -GNinja .. -DOQS_USE_OPENSSL=ON -DOQS_USE_CPU_EXTENSIONS=ON -DBUILD_SHARED_LIBS=ON -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/opt/local -DOQS_KEM_DEFAULT="OQS_KEM_alg_ntru_hrss701" -DOQS_SIG_DEFAULT="OQS_SIG_alg_dilithium_4" -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release

# Build
ninja

# Generate Doxygen docs
time ninja gen_docs
echo ""
echo "Built Doxygen documentation"
echo ""

# Run tests
time ninja run_tests
#echo "If you want to run tests - do "
#echo "   cd build && ninja run_tests"
echo ""

# Print start and end time - how long it all took
DATE_END="`date`"
echo ""
echo "Start: ${DATE_START}"
echo "End:   ${DATE_END}"

echo ""
echo "Completed."
echo ""
echo "To install: cd build && sudo ninja install"
echo ""

exit 0
```
